Compilation instructions:

This project uses GNU Build System for compilation and distribution. 

Here is an example script to configure compilation:

***********************************************************************************************
#!/bin/sh
./configure 	--prefix=/install_path \
				      --with-opencb=/OpenCB_install_path \
				      CFLAGS="-O0 -g -pg -std=c99 -Wall -D_REENTRANT -D_XOPEN_SOURCE=600 -fPIC"	#For debug compilation
***********************************************************************************************

Next, execute "make" for compilation and "make install" to install the program in prefix path.
In this example the program is compiled with debug like flags. 
For an optimized compilation use other flags like "-O3".


Utilization instructions:

Recalibrator is compiled on a binary executable by default, named "recal" and is in /install_path/bin path.

Here is an example script to call recal:
***********************************************************************************************
bin/recal -C 150 	-R "/path_to_reference_binary/dna_compression.bin" \
			            -I "/path_to_bam/input.bam" \
			            -o "/path_to_output/output.bam" \
			            -d "binary.data" -i "text.info"
***********************************************************************************************

For an explanation of program options execute "recal --help".
